           content: "width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" }

  %body
    %header{class: 'container'}
      %img{src: '/GJS_small.png'}
      %h1{id: 'logo'}
        Glasgow.js
        %br
        %span{class: 'subheading'}The Glasgow JavaScript User Group

      %aside{class: 'hidden-phone'}
        %ul{class: 'nav-pills'}
          %li
            %a{href: '#location'}
              %i{class: "icon-screenshot icon-white"}
              Where?
          %li
            %a{href: 'http://lanyrd.com/2012/glasgowjs/'}
              %i{class: "icon-pencil icon-white"}
              Sign up

    %section{class: 'container', id: 'next-meetup'}
      .row
        .span8
          %h1{id: 'meeting-date'}
            Next Meeting:
            %span{class: 'highlight'}
              Tuesday 4th of September

          %article{id: 'next-meeting'}
            .speaker
              .avatar-container
                %img{class: 'speaker-avatar', src: "http://a0.twimg.com/profile_images/2544873515/92c31799-b18c-4b29-b6bd-3f7e47a876cc_normal.jpg"}
              %h2 JS Continuous integration
              %h3 Rich Quick
              :markdown
                Improving the quality of your build should be paramount for effective, frequent releases. But how do we approach JS testing in the browser for our CI workflow? Rich knows best!

                Rich Quick (besides having a cool name) is a developer based in Glasgow working for Arnold Clark and has a who's who list of clients under his belt.He has even written a best selling book

              .connect
                %a{href: 'http://www.richquick.tv/'}richquick.tv
                %a{href: 'https://twitter.com/richquick'}@richquick

            .speaker
              .avatar-container
                %img{class: 'speaker-avatar', src: "http://a0.twimg.com/profile_images/1117688381/jollification_normal.jpg"}
              %h2 Lightning Talks
              %h3 Anyone brave enough
              :markdown
                This month see the first of our lightning talks sessions. They are 10 minute JavaScript quick fixes. So if you have something cool to talkabout stick your name on the board!

              .connect

        .span4
          #sponsors
            %h3 Our illustrious Sponsors

            %a{href: 'http://emergeadapt.com'}
              %img{src: '/images/emerge-adapt.png', alt: 'EmergeAdapt'}

            %a{href: 'http://newcontext.com'}
              %img{src: '/images/new_context_trimmed.png', alt: 'New Context'}

    #location
      %section{class: 'container'}
        %h1 Where to find us
        .row
          .span4
            :markdown
              ## Strachclyde University
              Graham Hills Building, Room GH515

              The metup starts at 6:30 with the first session starting at 7pm.

              Let us know you are coming by marking your attendance at [Lanyrd](http://lanyrd.com/2012/glasgow-js/)
